(GRUNTS)

274
00:22:09.762 --> 00:22:11.498
Universal translation.

275
00:22:11.598 --> 00:22:14.133
You hear Yautja.
others hear their language...

276
00:22:14.233 --> 00:22:15.668
- (CREATURE SQUAWKING)
- (GROWLS)

277
00:22:15.768 --> 00:22:17.704
- THIA: Oh. boy.
- (SQUAWKS)

278
00:22:18.638 --> 00:22:20.172
This isn't great for you.

279
00:22:20.272 --> 00:22:22.341
(SHRIEKS)

280
00:22:25.378 --> 00:22:30.216
(SCREECHING)

281
00:22:30.316 --> 00:22:31.551
(THUD)

282
00:22:34.153 --> 00:22:35.888
(GRUNTS)

283
00:22:37.757 --> 00:22:40.793
- (HISSING)
- (GRUMBLES)

284
00:22:40.893 --> 00:22:43.262
THIA: It waits
for the needles to paralyze you.

285
00:22:44.296 --> 00:22:47.033
Then eats you
while you can't move.

286
00:22:47.133 --> 00:22:49.636
(GROANS. ROARS. CLICKING)

287
00:22:54.173 --> 00:22:58.511
I could help you. but...
I need a hand.

288
00:22:59.211 --> 00:23:01.514
(CHUFFS. GRUNTS)

289
00:23:02.882 --> 00:23:05.084
(GRUNTS)

290
00:23:05.384 --> 00:23:07.696
(IN YAUTJA)
Yautja hunt alone.

291
00:23:07.720 --> 00:23:11.758
Yautja might hunt alone.
but they die alone too.

292
00:23:11.858 --> 00:23:14.427
(CHITTERING. GRUNTING)

293
00:23:14.961 --> 00:23:17.229
- Kalisk.
- (WHICKERS)

294
00:23:19.832 --> 00:23:22.569
- You're hunting the Kalisk.
- (METALLIC CLANG)

295
00:23:22.669 --> 00:23:24.704
(SHRIEKS)

296
00:23:24.804 --> 00:23:26.105
(THUD)

297
00:23:28.107 --> 00:23:29.842
(GASPING)

298
00:23:29.942 --> 00:23:31.077
(ROARS ANGRILY)

299
00:23:31.177 --> 00:23:32.244
(GRUNTS)

300
00:23:32.344 --> 00:23:33.746
(THORNS RICOCHETING)

301
00:23:34.514 --> 00:23:36.248
Gotta run faster.

302
00:23:38.150 --> 00:23:39.486
(GRUNTS. GASPS)

303
00:23:39.586 --> 00:23:41.588
(ROARS)

304
00:23:43.422 --> 00:23:45.191
THIA: It happens fast. huh?

305
00:23:45.291 --> 00:23:46.859
(PANTING)

306
00:23:46.959 --> 00:23:49.929
THIA: If you had a weapon.
you know. I could use it.

307
00:23:50.362 --> 00:23:52.264
(BEEPING)

308
00:23:53.966 --> 00:23:56.168
THIA: Throw me that.
and I can get you the antidote.

309
00:23:56.268 --> 00:23:58.605
- (BREATHING HEAVILY)
- (SHRIEKS)

310
00:23:58.705 --> 00:24:00.106
THIA: Now or never.

311
00:24:01.774 --> 00:24:03.976
(METALLIC WARBLING)

312
00:24:04.844 --> 00:24:06.045
(STRAINED GRUNTS)

313
00:24:08.447 --> 00:24:11.217
(GRUNTS)

314
00:24:12.018 --> 00:24:14.086
(GRUNTS)

315
00:24:17.724 --> 00:24:19.759
- (GROANS)
- (CREATURE SCREECHES)

316
00:24:25.231 --> 00:24:28.167
(CREATURE SQUAWKS)

317
00:24:28.267 --> 00:24:30.336
(ROARS)

318
00:24:31.070 --> 00:24:32.839
- (BLOWS LANDING)
- (CREATURE SQUAWKING)

319
00:24:32.939 --> 00:24:36.643
- (METALLIC STABBING)
- (SQUEALING)

320
00:24:37.677 --> 00:24:39.812
(PANTING) Hi.

321
00:24:43.049 --> 00:24:45.752
(SPEECH IN YAUTJA ECHOES)

322
00:24:48.487 --> 00:24:50.557
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

323
00:25:02.001 --> 00:25:04.270
THIA: Should be good as new.

324
00:25:04.737 --> 00:25:06.438
(GRUNTS)

325
00:25:09.441 --> 00:25:11.110
The venom makes them bloom.

326
00:25:11.210 --> 00:25:13.479
Also makes them
a handy antidote.

327
00:25:14.346 --> 00:25:15.582
(GRUNTS)

328
00:25:20.052 --> 00:25:21.688
How about a lift?

329
00:25:24.924 --> 00:25:26.759
- (LIGHT GROWL)
- Let's go.

330
00:25:29.696 --> 00:25:30.496
(GROWLS)

331
00:25:30.597 --> 00:25:32.231
Excuse you. sir.

332
00:25:33.170 --> 00:25:35.380
What happened to your legs?

333
00:25:35.434 --> 00:25:37.469
I'm synthetic.
I was built and deployed

334
00:25:37.570 --> 00:25:40.306
by the Weyland-Yutani
Corporation for research.

335
00:25:40.406 --> 00:25:42.942
Because their humans wouldn't
last a day on this planet.

336
00:25:43.042 --> 00:25:44.176
(CHUCKLES)
We found that--

337
00:25:44.276 --> 00:25:45.912
(THUDS)

338
00:25:46.012 --> 00:25:47.346
(SIGHS)

339
00:25:49.115 --> 00:25:50.817
(GRUNTS)

340
00:25:50.917 --> 00:25:52.885
Look... (SIGHS)

341
00:25:52.985 --> 00:25:56.155
Many Yautja have come
for the great Kalisk.

342
00:25:56.255 --> 00:25:58.625
and none have survived it...

343
00:25:58.725 --> 00:26:00.126
or Genna.

344
00:26:00.960 --> 00:26:02.161
(SIGHS)

345
00:26:03.262 --> 00:26:05.164
I've seen the Kalisk.

346
00:26:05.698 --> 00:26:07.299
I survived it.

347
00:26:08.434 --> 00:26:11.203
Here's my proposal:
You take me along with you.

348
00:26:11.303 --> 00:26:13.806
and I'll guide you to its den.

349
00:26:13.906 --> 00:26:16.275
Once there. I get my legs.

350
00:26:16.375 --> 00:26:18.010
you get your trophy.

351
00:26:18.110 --> 00:26:21.247
and everyone's a winner. Deal?

352
00:26:23.670 --> 00:26:26.000
You have seen the Kalisk?

353
00:26:27.053 --> 00:26:31.123
Oh. yeah. I've seen the Kalisk.

354
00:26:34.026 --> 00:26:35.261
(SCOFFS)

355
00:26:35.928 --> 00:26:37.864
(DEVICE BEEPS. WHIRS)

356
00:26:37.964 --> 00:26:41.600
(SIGHS)

357
00:26:42.902 --> 00:26:44.336
Okay. Hmm.

358
00:26:45.571 --> 00:26:47.707
- (GROWLS)
- (THIA SIGHS)

359
00:26:47.807 --> 00:26:49.575
Good luck with your journey.

360
00:26:50.777 --> 00:26:54.814
I'm just gonna...
go on my journey.

361
00:26:56.883 --> 00:26:58.918
I'm sure
you'll figure something out.

362
00:27:05.758 --> 00:27:08.494
Hey. (PANTING)

363
00:27:09.762 --> 00:27:12.832
I've already shown you
that I can be useful to you.

364
00:27:14.380 --> 00:27:16.250
Useful...

365
00:27:16.330 --> 00:27:17.960
like tool?

366
00:27:18.738 --> 00:27:22.742
Yes. Yes. exactly. like a tool.

367
00:27:22.842 --> 00:27:25.344
The only way to survive Genna
is to work with it.

368
00:27:25.444 --> 00:27:27.179
and I know how.

369
00:27:27.279 --> 00:27:30.416
And with the right tool...

370
00:27:31.884 --> 00:27:33.720
...you could get the Kalisk.

371
00:27:34.520 --> 00:27:35.888
You could be the first.

372
00:27:38.130 --> 00:27:40.580
I will use you. tool.

373
00:27:41.227 --> 00:27:43.629
You may call me Thi-- Whoa!

374
00:27:44.731 --> 00:27:48.868
You seem smaller than the other
Yautja. How old are you?

375
00:27:50.169 --> 00:27:51.738
And what does the chewing?

376
00:27:51.838 --> 00:27:54.306
Your outside fangs
or your inside teeth?

377
00:27:55.975 --> 00:27:58.577
Oh. What should I call you?

378
00:28:02.281 --> 00:28:03.783
- (GRUNTS)
- (YELPS)

379
00:28:04.550 --> 00:28:06.418
Whoa! (LAUGHS)

380
00:28:06.518 --> 00:28:09.321
I've never been thrown before.
What a... (DISTORTS) ...thrill!

381
00:28:09.421 --> 00:28:11.657
How fast were you going
when your ship crashed?

382
00:28:11.758 --> 00:28:15.094
Faster than sub-light speed?
We haven't cracked that yet.

383
00:28:15.194 --> 00:28:17.463
Also. that plasma sword
is interesting.

384
00:28:17.563 --> 00:28:18.965
Is it unique to your clan?

385
00:28:19.065 --> 00:28:20.366
And what may I call you?

386
00:28:21.433 --> 00:28:24.303
- I call these imbre anguis.
- (PROJECTILES HISSING)

387
00:28:34.113 --> 00:28:36.082
(PANTING)

388
00:28:36.182 --> 00:28:37.850
THIA: They just want a snack.

389
00:28:42.221 --> 00:28:45.091
(SQUEAKING)

390
00:28:45.191 --> 00:28:48.294
You catch more flies with honey
than you do with vinegar.

391
00:28:48.394 --> 00:28:50.129
(BUZZING)

392
00:28:50.250 --> 00:28:51.580
Don't want flies.

393
00:28:52.031 --> 00:28:55.868
Predatory organisms are
my specific area of expertise.

394
00:28:55.968 --> 00:28:59.305
I've studied Yautja extensively.
It's an impressive culture.

395
00:28:59.405 --> 00:29:00.840
(SIGHS)

396
00:29:00.940 --> 00:29:02.909
Here. ask me anything.
I bet I have the answer.

397
00:29:03.009 --> 00:29:04.443
- (EXHALES)
- Oh! (THUDS)

398
00:29:04.543 --> 00:29:05.744
(ANIMALS CALL DISTANTLY)

399
00:29:05.845 --> 00:29:07.246
Very funny.

400
00:29:07.346 --> 00:29:09.081
And you still haven't
told me your name.

401
00:29:30.630 --> 00:29:32.380
Name is Dek.

402
00:29:33.380 --> 00:29:35.150
Now talk that way.

403
00:29:35.174 --> 00:29:37.043
Okay. sure.

404
00:29:37.643 --> 00:29:41.814
(SIGHS) Well. let's back up
and start at the beginning.

405
00:29:42.181 --> 00:29:45.251
Genna was formed
64 billion cycles ago.

406
00:29:45.351 --> 00:29:48.287
when a dying red dwarf star
in a neighboring system...

407
00:29:48.387 --> 00:29:50.456
(BEEPING)

408
00:29:55.561 --> 00:29:57.897
(WHIRRING)

409
00:29:59.465 --> 00:30:00.967
(CLICKING. WHIRRING)

410
00:30:01.067 --> 00:30:03.102
It's so beautiful.

411
00:30:03.669 --> 00:30:06.238
After all the time
I've been stuck here.

412
00:30:06.338 --> 00:30:08.407
I never get tired of the view.

413
00:30:09.460 --> 00:30:12.154
How long have you been here?

414
00:30:12.178 --> 00:30:15.781
Well. we arrived on Genna two
years ago. and we built a base.

415
00:30:15.882 --> 00:30:18.384
Then. I was in
the vulture's nest

416
00:30:18.484 --> 00:30:20.219
for the most exciting

417
00:30:20.319 --> 00:30:23.455
13 days. seven hours. 43 minutes

418
00:30:23.555 --> 00:30:25.424
and two seconds of my life.

419
00:30:25.524 --> 00:30:26.993
(EXHALES)

420
00:30:27.093 --> 00:30:29.061
But I always knew
someone would come.

421
00:30:30.062 --> 00:30:32.398
I was just wrong about who.

422
00:30:33.920 --> 00:30:35.750
Who would come?

423
00:30:39.005 --> 00:30:40.372
Tessa.

424
00:30:41.874 --> 00:30:45.411
Our crew is made up
entirely of synths.

425
00:30:45.511 --> 00:30:47.379
But Tessa and I are special.

426
00:30:47.980 --> 00:30:50.382
We have a higher sensitivity
than the others.

427
00:30:50.710 --> 00:30:53.580
Sensitivity is weakness.

428
00:30:56.255 --> 00:30:58.424
Sensitivity is what allows us
to understand

429
00:30:58.524 --> 00:31:00.426
the creatures on this planet.

430
00:31:04.096 --> 00:31:06.332
We were created
to work in tandem.

431
00:31:07.133 --> 00:31:11.137
Me. cooped up in the lab.
Tessa out in the field.

432
00:31:11.237 --> 00:31:14.573
Until the wonderful day
Tessa let me come with her.

433
00:31:14.673 --> 00:31:16.909
We were exploring Genna.

434
00:31:18.277 --> 00:31:21.413
And then the Kalisk attacked us.

435
00:31:22.514 --> 00:31:25.985
Separated me... and us.

436
00:31:28.587 --> 00:31:31.623
The last sound
I remember hearing

437
00:31:31.723 --> 00:31:35.094
was Tessa calling out my name.

438
00:31:35.761 --> 00:31:37.429
Reaching for me.

439
00:31:39.231 --> 00:31:41.033
Then the Kalisk.

440
00:31:42.234 --> 00:31:43.936
I didn't know what to do.

441
00:31:45.137 --> 00:31:48.740
(DEK SNORING)

442
00:31:55.114 --> 00:31:57.783
But I refuse
to believe she's dead.

443
00:32:00.186 --> 00:32:05.324
(BEEPING)

444
00:32:10.529 --> 00:32:15.067
(HYDRAULICS HISSING)

445
00:32:15.167 --> 00:32:16.167
(THUDS)

446
00:32:17.403 --> 00:32:19.471
(WHIRRING)

447
00:32:23.675 --> 00:32:25.544
- (CLICKS)
- (ELECTRONIC WARBLE)

448
00:32:33.485 --> 00:32:35.487
Thia. Thia. Thia. Thia.

449
00:32:35.587 --> 00:32:36.422
(GUNFIRE)

450
00:32:36.522 --> 00:32:38.957
Thia. Thia. Thia...

451
00:32:39.725 --> 00:32:41.994
THIA: Tessa! (YELLING)

452
00:32:42.094 --> 00:32:43.094
(ROARS)

453
00:32:43.462 --> 00:32:45.831
Thia. Thia. Thia. Thia.

454
00:32:45.931 --> 00:32:47.333
Thia. Thia.

455
00:32:47.433 --> 00:32:50.469
(WHIRRING)

456
00:32:56.642 --> 00:32:58.577
(WHIRRING)

457
00:33:06.652 --> 00:33:08.720
(BUZZING)

458
00:33:18.264 --> 00:33:20.332
(ELECTRONIC CHIRPING)

459
00:33:20.432 --> 00:33:22.501
(GASPS)

460
00:33:24.336 --> 00:33:26.805
(WHIRRING)

461
00:33:26.905 --> 00:33:28.874
MUTHUR: Hello. Tessa.

462
00:33:28.974 --> 00:33:31.643
The Company is not pleased.

463
00:33:33.445 --> 00:33:36.848
Continued failure will result
in your decommission.

464
00:33:40.386 --> 00:33:42.221
Where's Thia?

465
00:33:45.524 --> 00:33:47.493
MUTHUR: The Yautja has Thia.

466
00:33:50.929 --> 00:33:54.300
(CREATURES CHITTERING)

467
00:33:56.268 --> 00:33:58.504
(CAWING)

468
00:33:58.604 --> 00:34:00.948
(IN YAUTJA)
I must eat.

469
00:34:00.972 --> 00:34:04.009
THIA: Two warriors.
Dek and Thia. on the hunt.

470
00:34:04.610 --> 00:34:06.078
Oh.

471
00:34:06.178 --> 00:34:07.846
Quick question.

472
00:34:07.946 --> 00:34:09.248
What should I be doing?

473
00:34:09.348 --> 00:34:10.949
(CHUFFS)

474
00:34:11.049 --> 00:34:12.718
(ANIMAL GROWLS)

475
00:34:13.460 --> 00:34:15.500
What is this creature?

476
00:34:16.888 --> 00:34:19.458
THIA: Bone bison.
They're Kalisk food.

477
00:34:19.558 --> 00:34:21.127
(GROWLING)

478
00:34:21.227 --> 00:34:24.830
DEK: Then it will be my food. too.

479
00:34:24.863 --> 00:34:28.234
So exciting.
Hunting with a Yautja.

480
00:34:28.334 --> 00:34:29.444
- (GROWLS)
- Tessa wouldn't believe it.

481
00:34:29.468 --> 00:34:30.836
(CHUFFS. CLICKS)

482
00:34:31.937 --> 00:34:33.205
- Just a warning...
- (GROWLS)

483
00:34:33.330 --> 00:34:34.960
Quiet tool!

484
00:34:36.208 --> 00:34:37.543
(YELPS. GROWLS)

485
00:34:38.377 --> 00:34:39.378
(QUIETLY) Razor grass.

486
00:34:39.478 --> 00:34:40.812
(CLINKS)

487
00:34:43.014 --> 00:34:45.851
It'll cut you to ribbons.
We'll just go around.

488
00:34:48.750 --> 00:34:51.040
You give up too easily.

489
00:34:52.591 --> 00:34:54.760
(CREATURE CHITTERING)

490
00:34:55.026 --> 00:34:57.329
We might not be alone
in this hunt.

491
00:34:58.464 --> 00:35:00.832
(BEEPING)

492
00:35:00.932 --> 00:35:02.201
(WHIRRING)

493
00:35:03.902 --> 00:35:06.305
- (HISSES)
- (SHOUTS)

494
00:35:07.606 --> 00:35:09.007
What an odd critter.

495
00:35:09.107 --> 00:35:11.143
I've never seen you before.

496
00:35:11.510 --> 00:35:12.678
(HISSES)

497
00:35:13.812 --> 00:35:15.681
(ROARS)

498
00:35:16.648 --> 00:35:18.617
Thia. Nice to meet you.

499
00:35:19.151 --> 00:35:20.752
- (SCOFFS)
- (SPRINGING CLICK)

500
00:35:20.852 --> 00:35:22.288
(GRUNTS)

501
00:35:23.155 --> 00:35:25.657
(GROWLS. ROARS)

502
00:35:32.298 --> 00:35:33.865
(CLICKING)

503
00:35:33.965 --> 00:35:35.577
Looks like your competition
is better-- (GASPS)

504
00:35:35.601 --> 00:35:37.603
(GROWLING)

505
00:35:53.319 --> 00:35:55.954
Careful up in these trees.
There are Luna bugs!

506
00:35:56.054 --> 00:35:57.094
- (THIA YELPS)
- (DEK GRUNTS)

507
00:35:58.657 --> 00:36:02.328
(STRAINED GROANS)

508
00:36:02.428 --> 00:36:04.863
(GASPING)

509
00:36:04.963 --> 00:36:07.866
(FOOTSTEPS RUMBLING)

510
00:36:07.966 --> 00:36:10.802
(ROARS)

511
00:36:10.902 --> 00:36:12.604
(BONE BISON ROARS)

512
00:36:17.175 --> 00:36:18.510
THIA: Coming up behind you!

513
00:36:18.610 --> 00:36:20.412
- (CHITTERS)
- (ROARS)

514
00:36:21.112 --> 00:36:23.181
(CHITTERING)

515
00:36:25.417 --> 00:36:26.985
(CREATURE SHRIEKS)

516
00:36:28.086 --> 00:36:30.188
(BOTH GRUNTING)

517
00:36:30.556 --> 00:36:31.556
(GRUNTS)

518
00:36:32.190 --> 00:36:33.592
THIA: Stronger than it looks!

519
00:36:40.499 --> 00:36:41.933
(GAGS. SHRIEKS)

520
00:36:43.602 --> 00:36:46.472
- (SCREECHES)
- Uh. Dek?

521
00:36:46.572 --> 00:36:49.074
- (YELPS)
- Dek! Look!

522
00:36:49.174 --> 00:36:50.409
(CREATURE ROARS)

523
00:36:53.312 --> 00:36:54.680
(GROWLS)

524
00:36:56.448 --> 00:36:58.250
(TRUMPETS)

525
00:36:59.551 --> 00:37:01.553
(SLOWED METALLIC SCRAPE)

526
00:37:13.599 --> 00:37:17.469
(SQUELCHING)

527
00:37:21.840 --> 00:37:22.908
(GRUNTS)

528
00:37:26.211 --> 00:37:27.679
(ROARS)

529
00:37:29.014 --> 00:37:30.849
(THIA YELLS)

530
00:37:33.352 --> 00:37:34.496
DEK: Kalisk?

531
00:37:34.520 --> 00:37:35.787
THIA: Not a Kalisk.

532
00:37:37.989 --> 00:37:40.091
This is a Luna bug!

533
00:37:40.191 --> 00:37:42.594
(RUMBLING)

534
00:37:42.694 --> 00:37:44.563
(DEEP CHITTERING)

535
00:37:46.365 --> 00:37:47.999
(ROARS)

536
00:37:48.099 --> 00:37:49.501
THIA: Have any other weapons?

537
00:37:49.601 --> 00:37:50.969
(METALLIC CLINKING. BEEPING)

538
00:37:51.903 --> 00:37:55.006
(LUNA BUG GROWLING)

539
00:37:59.378 --> 00:38:02.047
- (SCREECHES)
- (CRUNCHING)

540
00:38:02.147 --> 00:38:04.816
- (CREATURE GROWLS)
- (THIA YELLING)

541
00:38:04.916 --> 00:38:07.753
(GRUNTS)

542
00:38:11.890 --> 00:38:14.993
- (INHALES. GRUNTS)
- (CREATURE SQUAWKS)

543
00:38:15.093 --> 00:38:18.430
- (GROWLS)
- (MURMURS)

544
00:38:18.530 --> 00:38:20.098
(ROARS)

545
00:38:20.999 --> 00:38:23.869
(ROARING)

546
00:38:24.570 --> 00:38:25.637
(SNARLS)

547
00:38:30.709 --> 00:38:33.412
- (PANTING)
- (ROARS)

548
00:38:35.213 --> 00:38:37.082
(CHITTERING)

549
00:38:38.550 --> 00:38:40.519
- (PANTING)
- (SHRIEKS)

550
00:38:42.220 --> 00:38:44.289
(GROWLING)

551
00:38:44.390 --> 00:38:46.358
(FOOTSTEPS THUNDERING)

552
00:38:46.458 --> 00:38:48.494
Why'd you stop?
Let's get out of here.

553
00:38:49.040 --> 00:38:50.920
You give up too easily.

554
00:38:52.230 --> 00:38:54.165
(CRACKLING)

555
00:38:55.667 --> 00:38:58.036
(CHITTERING)

556
00:39:02.874 --> 00:39:04.075
(ROARS)

557
00:39:05.644 --> 00:39:07.078
(ROARS)

558
00:39:09.515 --> 00:39:12.951
(FEARFUL CHITTERING)

559
00:39:20.926 --> 00:39:23.061
(GROWLS)

560
00:39:25.731 --> 00:39:27.533
(ROARS)

561
00:39:29.668 --> 00:39:32.638
(CHITTERS. MURMURS)

562
00:39:41.046 --> 00:39:44.683
(PANTING)

563
00:39:46.718 --> 00:39:49.521
(ANIMALS CHIRP. CHITTER)

564
00:39:53.525 --> 00:39:55.393
(CHIRPS)

565
00:40:11.443 --> 00:40:13.311
(SCREECHING)

566
00:40:16.281 --> 00:40:18.249
(CHITTERS. SCREECHES)

567
00:40:28.694 --> 00:40:29.895
(GUN CLICKS)

568
00:40:35.501 --> 00:40:36.802
(CHITTERS)

569
00:40:37.469 --> 00:40:38.804
(SCREECHES)

570
00:40:39.638 --> 00:40:41.306
(FLAMES ROARING)

571
00:40:41.640 --> 00:40:43.509
That was the best hunt
I've ever been on.

572
00:40:43.609 --> 00:40:45.043
This is the dream team
right here.

573
00:40:45.143 --> 00:40:47.546
The Dynamic Three.
The Dynamic Trio.

574
00:40:47.646 --> 00:40:49.380
The Dynamic Tree-oh!

575
00:40:49.481 --> 00:40:51.583
Tree-oh! Remember when
we went down the tree?

576
00:40:51.683 --> 00:40:53.284
That monster's mouth. I mean...

577
00:40:53.384 --> 00:40:54.920
(DISGUSTED MOAN)

578
00:40:55.020 --> 00:40:56.664
Didn't smell great.
didn't smell great. But...

579
00:40:56.688 --> 00:40:58.156
(THIA SIGHS)

580
00:40:58.256 --> 00:41:00.759
We got him. We got him.
And then we met you.

581
00:41:00.859 --> 00:41:03.495
our little sweet.
little. little thing.

582
00:41:03.595 --> 00:41:05.997
Thank you. seriously.
for that experience.

583
00:41:06.097 --> 00:41:08.700
Truly amazing. Thrilling.

584
00:41:08.800 --> 00:41:11.236
Truly thrilling.
What was your favorite part?

585
00:41:11.336 --> 00:41:13.605
- (CHITTERS)
- (WHICKERS)

586
00:41:14.305 --> 00:41:18.040
(IN YAUTJA)
When I pierced its head with my sword.

587
00:41:18.500 --> 00:41:22.210
and its blood rushed down my face.

588
00:41:24.382 --> 00:41:25.551
Cool.

589
00:41:26.918 --> 00:41:29.287
(CHITTERS SOFTLY)

590
00:41:33.959 --> 00:41:38.063
Oh. No. thanks. I don't eat.
but that's very sweet.

591
00:41:40.000 --> 00:41:42.330
This flesh is not sweet.

592
00:41:43.434 --> 00:41:44.670
Good to know.

593
00:41:44.970 --> 00:41:47.606
(CHITTERS. SQUEAKS)

594
00:41:48.139 --> 00:41:49.139
(STOPS)

595
00:41:49.775 --> 00:41:51.743
Our little bud here
looks hungry.

596
00:41:54.212 --> 00:41:55.313
(DEK CHUFFS)

597
00:41:56.447 --> 00:41:57.616
(SQUEAKS)

598
00:42:01.486 --> 00:42:03.321
(SPITS. CHITTERS)

599
00:42:03.421 --> 00:42:04.421
(ROARS)

600
00:42:04.489 --> 00:42:06.424
I think she's marking you.

601
00:42:06.792 --> 00:42:08.994
She wants you
to be a part of her clan.

602
00:42:09.761 --> 00:42:10.962
(MUNCHES)

603
00:42:11.062 --> 00:42:11.963
Maybe she's lost.

604
00:42:12.080 --> 00:42:14.408
I have no clan!

605
00:42:14.432 --> 00:42:18.169
What do you mean?
Don't all Yautja have family?

606
00:42:18.670 --> 00:42:20.420
No clan.

607
00:42:22.140 --> 00:42:24.375
So you never had anyone
looking out for you?

608
00:42:26.710 --> 00:42:29.710
I had a brother.

609
00:42:30.281 --> 00:42:31.281
Had?

610
00:42:34.385 --> 00:42:35.754
What happened to him?

611
00:42:37.750 --> 00:42:41.290
Father killed him.

612
00:42:44.129 --> 00:42:45.563
You're grieving.

613
00:42:45.964 --> 00:42:46.998
(CHITTERS)

614
00:42:47.130 --> 00:42:49.790
Grief is weakness.

615
00:42:52.938 --> 00:42:55.373
You're here
because you lost your brother.

616
00:42:56.290 --> 00:42:59.630
I am here for Kalisk.

617
00:43:01.710 --> 00:43:04.500
Why are you here?

618
00:43:08.353 --> 00:43:10.055
I'm here
because traveling with you

619
00:43:10.155 --> 00:43:12.490
is the best way
to get back to Tessa.

620
00:43:14.425 --> 00:43:16.027
When I was
in that vulture's nest.

621
00:43:16.127 --> 00:43:18.797
I was so afraid
I would never see her again.

622
00:43:19.330 --> 00:43:22.670
You should be able to survive on your own.

623
00:43:23.735 --> 00:43:26.004
I can survive on my own.

624
00:43:27.438 --> 00:43:29.875
But who would want
to survive on their own?

625
00:43:34.830 --> 00:43:37.959
Tessa is your sister.

626
00:43:37.983 --> 00:43:39.450
(WHICKERS)

627
00:43:41.853 --> 00:43:43.288
Sister.

628
00:43:46.224 --> 00:43:47.325
Yeah.

629
00:43:48.059 --> 00:43:49.795
I guess she is.

630
00:43:51.562 --> 00:43:54.866
I have... a sister.

631
00:43:55.633 --> 00:43:56.835
(CHUCKLES)

632
00:43:57.602 --> 00:43:59.637
What a lovely thought.

633
00:44:04.509 --> 00:44:06.044
I need to find her.

634
00:44:08.330 --> 00:44:09.830
And legs.

635
00:44:10.648 --> 00:44:12.083
Excuse me?

636
00:44:13.210 --> 00:44:14.790
Find your sister.

637
00:44:15.830 --> 00:44:17.710
And legs.

638
00:44:20.025 --> 00:44:21.559
Was that a joke?

639
00:44:22.060 --> 00:44:25.396
- (WHICKERS)
- (CHUCKLES)

640
00:44:38.309 --> 00:44:40.145
(WHICKERS. CHUFFS)

641
00:44:45.884 --> 00:44:47.185
(GRUNTS)

642
00:44:53.624 --> 00:44:55.727
(YAWNING)

643
00:44:56.427 --> 00:44:59.765
(YAWNING)

644
00:45:02.000 --> 00:45:03.101
(CHUFFS)

645
00:45:08.406 --> 00:45:10.809
- (ELECTRONIC HUMMING)
- (CHUFFS)

646
00:45:17.048 --> 00:45:19.017
(MURMURS)

647
00:45:19.885 --> 00:45:21.119
(CHITTERS)

648
00:45:21.219 --> 00:45:22.553
(METALLIC SCRAPE)

649
00:45:23.154 --> 00:45:24.890
(ENGINES WHIRRING)

650
00:45:26.858 --> 00:45:28.159
(WHIRRING SLOWS)

651
00:45:42.007 --> 00:45:44.142
(WHIRRING)

652
00:45:48.713 --> 00:45:49.915
(THUDS)

653
00:46:08.233 --> 00:46:10.101
(BEEPING. CHIRPING)

654
00:46:27.252 --> 00:46:29.187
(ELECTRONIC BEEPING)

655
00:46:30.488 --> 00:46:31.857
(METALLIC SCRAPING)

656
00:46:39.464 --> 00:46:40.966
(THUDS. RUMBLES)

657
00:46:45.436 --> 00:46:47.138
(CLANKS)

658
00:47:20.972 --> 00:47:23.008
(CLICKS. HISSES)

659
00:47:40.591 --> 00:47:41.726
(IN YAUTJA)
The sun rises.

660
00:47:42.630 --> 00:47:43.790
Let's go.

661
00:47:43.895 --> 00:47:45.496
We can't leave Bud.

662
00:47:46.131 --> 00:47:47.432
Bud?

663
00:47:47.532 --> 00:47:50.635
- Yeah. Bud. I named her.
- (BUD SNORING)

664
00:47:51.130 --> 00:47:53.500
Yautja hunt alone.

665
00:47:55.106 --> 00:47:57.342
You're not alone. I'm with you.

666
00:47:57.842 --> 00:47:58.709
(CHUFFS)

667
00:47:58.830 --> 00:48:00.330
You're a tool.

668
00:48:05.016 --> 00:48:06.417
(GRUNTS)

669
00:48:06.517 --> 00:48:08.886
The tree would have eaten us
without her.

670
00:48:09.687 --> 00:48:10.688
(SIGHS)

671
00:48:10.790 --> 00:48:14.380
We're not in the tree now.

672
00:48:24.902 --> 00:48:30.008
(CREATURES SCREECHING)

673
00:48:33.945 --> 00:48:37.615
(SCREECHING. GRUMBLING)

674
00:49:00.671 --> 00:49:02.740
(WHICKERS)

675
00:49:09.790 --> 00:49:11.880
Kalisk?

676
00:49:17.420 --> 00:49:19.210
It drinks here.

677
00:49:21.580 --> 00:49:23.750
It drinks here?

678
00:49:26.880 --> 00:49:30.960
You are a useless tool if you don't speak.

679
00:49:35.973 --> 00:49:37.575
Bud saved us.

680
00:49:39.177 --> 00:49:42.147
She spit on you to claim you
as part of her family.

681
00:49:48.019 --> 00:49:50.121
Why'd your father
kill your brother?

682
00:49:57.540 --> 00:50:00.420
My brother was protecting me.

683
00:50:01.399 --> 00:50:02.833
(SIGHS)

684
00:50:05.670 --> 00:50:09.000
The clan can have no weakness.

685
00:50:10.210 --> 00:50:12.750
I will show them strength.

686
00:50:18.883 --> 00:50:20.118
On Earth...

687
00:50:21.552 --> 00:50:23.821
there's a predator known
as the wolf.

688
00:50:23.921 --> 00:50:25.556
It's a powerful creature.

689
00:50:28.426 --> 00:50:29.927
They hunt in packs.

690
00:50:30.461 --> 00:50:31.929
They're very loyal.

691
00:50:32.897 --> 00:50:35.633
The leader of the pack
is the alpha.

692
00:50:35.733 --> 00:50:37.668
Known as the most dominant.

693
00:50:37.968 --> 00:50:39.813
(IN ENGLISH)
Wolf.

694
00:50:39.837 --> 00:50:42.973
(IN YAUTJA)
This alpha must be a great killer.

695
00:50:43.380 --> 00:50:45.386
I will hunt it too.

696
00:50:45.410 --> 00:50:46.410
THIA: No.

697
00:50:46.877 --> 00:50:50.981
The alpha isn't the wolf
who kills the most.

698
00:50:52.217 --> 00:50:56.987
The alpha is actually the one
who best protects the pack.

699
00:50:58.920 --> 00:51:00.580
I see...

700
00:51:02.880 --> 00:51:07.130
But I will be the alpha
that kills the most.

701
00:51:41.630 --> 00:51:43.460
The Kalisk's den?

702
00:51:59.550 --> 00:52:01.619
(FOOTSTEPS LANDING)

703
00:52:11.880 --> 00:52:13.710
Who are they?

704
00:52:15.233 --> 00:52:17.134
Weyland-Yutani synths.

705
00:52:19.069 --> 00:52:22.106
The Kalisk destroyed
most of our mission team.

706
00:52:26.877 --> 00:52:28.813
(GASPS) There I am.

707
00:52:32.750 --> 00:52:33.750
(THUD)

708
00:52:34.352 --> 00:52:35.386
(SIGHS)

709
00:52:44.862 --> 00:52:46.797
(BEEPS)

710
00:52:47.798 --> 00:52:48.866
(WHIRS)

711
00:52:52.002 --> 00:52:54.104
(WHIRRING)

712
00:52:55.506 --> 00:52:58.243
(ELECTRONIC BLIPS)

713
00:53:02.847 --> 00:53:04.282
(CHARGES)

714
00:53:04.382 --> 00:53:06.116
(THUDS)

715
00:53:12.210 --> 00:53:13.920
Easier to walk now.

716
00:53:14.559 --> 00:53:15.826
It's about to be.

717
00:53:16.794 --> 00:53:17.794
No.

718
00:53:18.290 --> 00:53:20.670
Easier for me to walk now.

719
00:53:22.567 --> 00:53:25.803
Oh. Of course. Right.

720
00:53:28.473 --> 00:53:29.874
Thank you. Dek.

721
00:53:32.510 --> 00:53:34.412
I'm never gonna forget this.

722
00:53:34.945 --> 00:53:36.080
(WHICKERS)

723
00:53:36.750 --> 00:53:39.380
I too will remember this...

724
00:53:39.710 --> 00:53:43.580
today I become Dek of the Yautja.

725
00:53:44.330 --> 00:53:47.170
I will honor Kwei...

726
00:53:48.750 --> 00:53:52.040
when I bring the Kalisk home.

727
00:53:54.080 --> 00:53:57.380
Then I taste revenge.

728
00:53:58.880 --> 00:54:02.330
You will be the first to see my trophy.

729
00:54:04.170 --> 00:54:06.130
It is a great honor.

730
00:54:07.210 --> 00:54:08.670
For you.

731
00:54:09.680 --> 00:54:12.283
Dek. there's something
I have to tell you.

732
00:54:13.884 --> 00:54:15.453
You need to leave now.

733
00:54:16.754 --> 00:54:18.923
FEMALE ELECTRONIC VOICE:
Location beacon activated.

734
00:54:19.040 --> 00:54:20.040
What?

735
00:54:20.758 --> 00:54:22.960
I called Tessa.
The company is on its way.

736
00:54:23.060 --> 00:54:24.895
You can't be here
when they arrive.

737
00:54:25.080 --> 00:54:28.080
I came here for the Kalisk.

738
00:54:28.666 --> 00:54:29.767
(SIGHS)

739
00:54:30.267 --> 00:54:31.869
So did I. Dek.

740
00:54:32.570 --> 00:54:35.873
The company sent us here
to capture the Kalisk.

741
00:54:36.000 --> 00:54:38.420
You want my trophy.

742
00:54:41.790 --> 00:54:43.960
Where is the Kalisk?

743
00:54:45.149 --> 00:54:48.285
Dek. you can't kill it.

744
00:54:48.540 --> 00:54:53.033
I use you. tool. You do not use me!

745
00:54:53.057 --> 00:54:54.892
I'm sorry. You have to leave.

746
00:54:55.760 --> 00:54:57.995
I needed you
to help bring me here.

747
00:54:58.130 --> 00:55:00.630
I use you!

748
00:55:02.580 --> 00:55:05.040
Where is the Kalisk?

749
00:55:05.069 --> 00:55:06.871
I'm trying to help you. Dek.

750
00:55:08.773 --> 00:55:10.608
You think your brother
saved your life

751
00:55:10.708 --> 00:55:12.577
just so you could die here?

752
00:55:14.500 --> 00:55:18.580
Then my death will be honorable.

753
00:55:21.218 --> 00:55:22.387
(CHUFFS SOFTLY)

754
00:55:24.330 --> 00:55:26.330
Call your sister.

755
00:55:27.290 --> 00:55:29.540
None can stop me.

756
00:55:30.728 --> 00:55:32.062
(SIGHS)

757
00:55:36.066 --> 00:55:38.135
(CLICKING)

758
00:55:43.441 --> 00:55:45.175
(ELECTRONIC BEEPS. BLIPS)

759
00:55:58.355 --> 00:55:59.790
(SNIFFS)

760
00:56:01.759 --> 00:56:03.461
(WHICKERS)

761
00:56:13.738 --> 00:56:17.575
- (GROWLS)
- (EXPLOSION BOOMS)

762
00:56:19.710 --> 00:56:21.812
(SQUAWKING)

763
00:56:22.847 --> 00:56:25.683
(FOOTSTEPS STOMPING)

764
00:56:26.584 --> 00:56:28.586
(ELECTRONIC CHITTERS)

765
00:56:28.686 --> 00:56:32.056
(RUMBLING APPROACHES)

766
00:56:33.424 --> 00:56:36.961
(THUMPING)

767
00:56:46.604 --> 00:56:47.772
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

768
00:56:49.273 --> 00:56:52.142
(ROARS)

769
00:56:52.710 --> 00:56:55.680
(ROARS INTENSELY)

770
00:56:57.548 --> 00:57:00.818
(SERVOS WHIRRING)

771
00:57:00.918 --> 00:57:03.588
(SNARLS. GRUNTS)

772
00:57:09.460 --> 00:57:10.595
(METALLIC SCRAPE)

773
00:57:11.428 --> 00:57:13.798
(GROWLING)

774
00:57:15.132 --> 00:57:16.266
(GROWLS)

775
00:57:29.514 --> 00:57:32.617
- (PAINED HOWL)
- (PANTING)

776
00:57:32.717 --> 00:57:36.053
(KALISK SNARLS)

777
00:57:36.521 --> 00:57:38.589
(GROWLS)

778
00:57:45.062 --> 00:57:46.831
(GRUNTS)

779
00:57:47.798 --> 00:57:50.267
(WHIRRING)

780
00:57:50.968 --> 00:57:52.236
(GROANS)

781
00:57:52.336 --> 00:57:54.672
Ugh! Come on!

782
00:57:56.707 --> 00:57:58.709
(GROANS)

783
00:57:59.544 --> 00:58:02.012
- (ELECTRICAL CRACKLE)
- (THUDS)

784
00:58:14.792 --> 00:58:16.493
(GROWLS)

785
00:58:16.594 --> 00:58:18.663
(RUMBLING)

786
00:58:27.638 --> 00:58:30.741
- (ROARS)
- (GUNFIRE)

787
00:58:32.176 --> 00:58:34.511
(PAINED GRUNTS)

788
00:58:41.518 --> 00:58:42.553
(SCREAMS) Dek!

789
00:58:42.653 --> 00:58:43.921
- (ROARS)
- (METALLIC CLINK)

790
00:58:45.089 --> 00:58:46.323
(METALLIC WHIRRING)

791
00:58:46.423 --> 00:58:50.394
(GROWLING)

792
00:58:55.000 --> 00:58:57.040
Save yourself. tool!

793
00:59:02.239 --> 00:59:04.174
(ROARS)

794
00:59:11.215 --> 00:59:12.516
(PANTING)

795
00:59:19.256 --> 00:59:21.058
(SLOWED METALLIC SCRAPE)

796
00:59:21.626 --> 00:59:23.160
(SNARLS)

797
00:59:25.930 --> 00:59:27.998
(GRUNTS)

798
00:59:29.634 --> 00:59:32.236
(PANTING)

799
00:59:32.336 --> 00:59:35.105
(FLESH SQUELCHING)

800
00:59:38.142 --> 00:59:40.044
(SNARLS)

801
00:59:43.881 --> 00:59:45.750
(CRACKLES)

802
00:59:47.351 --> 00:59:48.886
(SNARLS)

803
00:59:48.986 --> 00:59:50.454
(GRUNTS)

804
00:59:52.356 --> 00:59:54.191
(ROARS)

805
00:59:54.291 --> 00:59:55.626
- (GRUNTS)
- (SNARLS)

806
00:59:55.726 --> 00:59:58.162
(SNIFFING)

807
01:00:04.769 --> 01:00:11.075
(SNIFFS. PURRS)

808
01:00:11.175 --> 01:00:13.577
(BEEPING)

809
01:00:19.549 --> 01:00:20.718
(CHUFFS)

810
01:00:21.551 --> 01:00:23.053
(ROARS. SILENCES)

811
01:00:26.090 --> 01:00:28.092
(STRAINED GRUNTS)

812
01:00:28.192 --> 01:00:29.994
(CRACKLING)

813
01:00:41.338 --> 01:00:43.340
(CHUFFS. SNARLS SOFTLY)

814
01:00:48.145 --> 01:00:51.816
(GRUNTING)

815
01:00:52.920 --> 01:00:55.420
Tool. get these off!

816
01:00:56.353 --> 01:00:57.688
(GRUNTS)

817
01:00:58.923 --> 01:01:01.258
(SNARLS)

818
01:01:03.127 --> 01:01:05.105
You are not Thia.

819
01:01:05.129 --> 01:01:06.129
(GRUNTS)

820
01:01:14.905 --> 01:01:16.673
(GROWLS)

821
01:01:17.580 --> 01:01:19.420
Release me!

822
01:01:22.380 --> 01:01:25.460
You are another broken tool!

823
01:01:26.383 --> 01:01:30.354
The Yautja cull their weak.
Why were you spared?

824
01:01:32.589 --> 01:01:34.558
(BEEPS. WHIRS)

825
01:01:37.127 --> 01:01:38.963
(THRUMMING)

826
01:01:40.540 --> 01:01:42.750
Remove these!

827
01:01:43.500 --> 01:01:48.710
Or I'll rip out your spine
and crush your skull!

828
01:01:49.774 --> 01:01:51.508
I read Thia's logs.

829
01:01:53.143 --> 01:01:56.080
You never told her
why your brother protected you.

830
01:01:58.380 --> 01:02:02.670
You are nothing. A device.

831
01:02:03.960 --> 01:02:07.580
Made by others to do their work for them.

832
01:02:08.092 --> 01:02:09.493
That's correct.

833
01:02:10.360 --> 01:02:14.064
And you are now property of the
Weyland-Yutani Corporation.

834
01:02:14.899 --> 01:02:18.202
It is a great honor. For you.

835
01:02:18.602 --> 01:02:19.403
(GRUNTS)

836
01:02:19.503 --> 01:02:21.171
(SNARLS. GROWLS)

837
01:02:32.516 --> 01:02:34.584
(FAINT BUZZING)

838
01:02:34.852 --> 01:02:36.921
(BLIPS. BUZZING)

839
01:02:39.857 --> 01:02:43.760
(WHIRRING. ELECTRONIC BLIPS)

840
01:02:50.801 --> 01:02:52.336
(WHISPERING) Tessa.

841
01:02:53.270 --> 01:02:54.371
(CHUFFS)

842
01:02:55.139 --> 01:02:56.673
You made it.

843
01:02:58.108 --> 01:02:59.309
We made it.

844
01:03:03.647 --> 01:03:05.182
I've seen so much.

845
01:03:05.850 --> 01:03:07.284
(THIA EXHALES)

846
01:03:07.818 --> 01:03:12.389
I have so much to tell you.
I saw such incredible creatures.

847
01:03:13.090 --> 01:03:16.393
The Yautja is a great
travelling companion.

848
01:03:18.028 --> 01:03:21.431
Thia.
You were right about the Kalisk.

849
01:03:21.540 --> 01:03:24.130
You betrayed me!

850
01:03:25.235 --> 01:03:27.771
The creature
is a regenerative miracle.

851
01:03:28.572 --> 01:03:30.640
Humanity will thank us.

852
01:03:33.677 --> 01:03:34.845
We have the Kalisk?

853
01:03:34.945 --> 01:03:35.945
Yes.

854
01:03:36.713 --> 01:03:39.884
And Muthur will be pleased
with your additional catch.

855
01:03:41.018 --> 01:03:42.119
(SNARLS)

856
01:03:42.219 --> 01:03:44.288
(ENRAGED GRUNTING)

857
01:03:44.821 --> 01:03:46.290
(GROWLING)

858
01:03:46.390 --> 01:03:47.858
Additional catch?

859
01:03:47.958 --> 01:03:51.028
(GROWLING. ROARING)

860
01:03:51.128 --> 01:03:52.362
(GRUNTS. SNARLS)

861
01:03:52.462 --> 01:03:56.967
(DEK STRAINING)

862
01:03:57.067 --> 01:03:59.870
The Yautja
is not an ideal specimen.

863
01:04:02.172 --> 01:04:05.275
No. not ideal.

864
01:04:05.375 --> 01:04:10.314
(SNARLS. GRUNTS)

865
01:04:11.882 --> 01:04:13.717
(DEVICE BEEPS)

866
01:04:13.817 --> 01:04:16.186
(SOFT SNARLS)

867
01:04:20.290 --> 01:04:22.392
(DEVICE WHIRS)

868
01:04:25.062 --> 01:04:26.062
(GROWLS)

869
01:04:27.131 --> 01:04:29.900
(HUFFS. GROANS)

870
01:04:30.000 --> 01:04:31.435
(SNARLS)

871
01:04:33.303 --> 01:04:35.472
But its technology is valuable.

872
01:04:36.506 --> 01:04:39.709
We can salvage its weapons
and leave the Yautja.

873
01:04:42.712 --> 01:04:43.914
Good idea.

874
01:04:47.217 --> 01:04:49.286
But it's so malformed.

875
01:04:50.687 --> 01:04:53.557
We're going to need a sample.
For research.

876
01:04:54.791 --> 01:04:56.460
- (BEEPS)
- (AGONIZED ROAR)

877
01:04:56.560 --> 01:04:57.861
(BEEPING)

878
01:04:57.962 --> 01:04:59.496
(DEK SNARLING. GROANING)

879
01:04:59.596 --> 01:05:01.665
(SNARLS. GRUNTS)

880
01:05:04.668 --> 01:05:06.303
He was not the goal
of our mission.

881
01:05:06.403 --> 01:05:08.705
(ELECTRONIC WHIRS)

882
01:05:08.805 --> 01:05:10.707
(GRUNTING)

883
01:05:10.807 --> 01:05:12.542
Tessa. he is deficient.

884
01:05:12.642 --> 01:05:14.578
(SHRIEKING)

885
01:05:14.678 --> 01:05:15.745
Tessa!

886
01:05:18.582 --> 01:05:20.050
(MACHINERY HALTS)

887
01:05:20.150 --> 01:05:21.986
(DEK GRUNTING)

888
01:05:31.695 --> 01:05:35.365
Thia.
this is what is asked of us.

889
01:05:40.170 --> 01:05:42.772
We can be more
than what they ask of us.

890
01:05:46.810 --> 01:05:48.578
What can we be?

891
01:05:50.880 --> 01:05:52.182
Sisters.

892
01:06:08.932 --> 01:06:10.167
Thia.

893
01:06:23.113 --> 01:06:25.949
Do you know why
Muthur gave us feelings?

894
01:06:28.318 --> 01:06:31.255
So we could understand
the creatures on this planet.

895
01:06:33.823 --> 01:06:35.059
(SNARLS)

896
01:06:36.426 --> 01:06:38.828
- And exploit them.
- Exploit them.

897
01:06:40.130 --> 01:06:41.831
The Yautja is different.

898
01:06:41.931 --> 01:06:43.467
(CHUFFS)

899
01:06:44.901 --> 01:06:49.005
He rescued me.
Like you rescued me.

900
01:06:50.840 --> 01:06:53.510
I did not come here
to rescue you.

901
01:06:54.611 --> 01:06:56.813
I am completing our mission.

902
01:06:58.382 --> 01:07:00.417
When we first faced the Kalisk.

903
01:07:01.685 --> 01:07:03.753
I tried to protect you.

904
01:07:05.822 --> 01:07:08.392
And that almost cost me
everything.

905
01:07:10.794 --> 01:07:12.896
What do you mean. Tessa?

906
01:07:14.064 --> 01:07:17.334
I almost made the same mistake
the Yautja's brother made.

907
01:07:17.801 --> 01:07:18.568
(CLICKS)

908
01:07:18.668 --> 01:07:21.505
The weak must be culled.

909
01:07:22.739 --> 01:07:26.310
And Thia. you're broken.

910
01:07:31.315 --> 01:07:32.315
(GRUNTS)

911
01:07:34.017 --> 01:07:36.720
Tessa. incoming message
from Muthur.

912
01:07:36.820 --> 01:07:39.156
Motivate the Yautja
to explain its weapons.

913
01:07:39.256 --> 01:07:40.390
And the unit?

914
01:07:43.560 --> 01:07:44.761
Box her up.

915
01:07:50.267 --> 01:07:51.868
(DOOR HISSES)

916
01:07:54.330 --> 01:07:56.040
I trusted you.

917
01:07:56.139 --> 01:07:58.074
(SNARLS. CLICKS)

918
01:08:00.310 --> 01:08:01.411
(HUFFS)

919
01:08:02.210 --> 01:08:04.490
Don't like these tools.

920
01:08:04.514 --> 01:08:07.000
(IN YAUTJA)
I'm sorry. My sister is--

921
01:08:07.080 --> 01:08:09.040
Don't like sister either.

922
01:08:10.187 --> 01:08:11.187
(SNARLS)

923
01:08:11.555 --> 01:08:13.590
Why are you speaking
its language?

924
01:08:16.710 --> 01:08:19.380
Tell tool you're asking about the device.

925
01:08:21.465 --> 01:08:22.832
You heard the orders.

926
01:08:22.932 --> 01:08:25.602
I'm asking it
to explain this device.

927
01:08:27.504 --> 01:08:28.805
What is the device?

928
01:08:29.806 --> 01:08:32.342
(IN YAUTJA)
He's asking about the device.

929
01:08:32.676 --> 01:08:35.345
DEK: It's a children's toy.

930
01:08:37.130 --> 01:08:39.790
But say it's a map.

931
01:08:40.484 --> 01:08:42.051
What did it say?

932
01:08:44.154 --> 01:08:45.689
He says it's a map.

933
01:08:46.923 --> 01:08:48.292
How does it work?

934
01:08:48.920 --> 01:08:51.710
Tell tool to look inside.

935
01:08:55.599 --> 01:08:56.700
(EXPLOSIVE PULSE)

936
01:09:00.170 --> 01:09:02.040
That was a toy for children?

937
01:09:02.130 --> 01:09:03.250
Yautja children!

938
01:09:06.109 --> 01:09:07.544
(DOOR BEEPS. HISSES)

939
01:09:08.812 --> 01:09:09.813
(ALARM BLARES)

940
01:09:09.920 --> 01:09:10.920
Run Dek!

941
01:09:13.080 --> 01:09:14.540
Go... Go!

942
01:09:17.354 --> 01:09:18.388
(CALLS OUT)

943
01:09:18.522 --> 01:09:19.522
Stop!

944
01:09:20.957 --> 01:09:22.226
(THIA STRAINING)

945
01:09:27.297 --> 01:09:30.267
(GRUNTING)

946
01:09:30.767 --> 01:09:32.602
(ROARING)

947
01:09:37.641 --> 01:09:39.709
(ENGINE HUMMING)

948
01:09:57.561 --> 01:09:59.296
(SNARLS)

949
01:09:59.963 --> 01:10:02.799
(GROWLS. CLICKING)

950
01:10:12.376 --> 01:10:15.044
(PANTING)

951
01:10:21.084 --> 01:10:22.552
(GRUNTS)

952
01:10:25.021 --> 01:10:26.290
(WINCES)

953
01:10:44.007 --> 01:10:45.375
(DEVICE BEEPS)

954
01:10:45.475 --> 01:10:46.743
(SHARP GRUNT)

955
01:10:48.512 --> 01:10:50.179
(DEVICE WARBLING)

956
01:10:50.647 --> 01:10:51.647
(WINCES)

957
01:10:52.181 --> 01:10:54.284
(GRUNTING)

958
01:11:09.232 --> 01:11:11.435
(GRUNT. ROARS)

959
01:11:14.471 --> 01:11:15.472
KWEI!

960
01:11:19.142 --> 01:11:21.210
(POWER WHIRRING)

961
01:11:22.712 --> 01:11:24.213
(ELECTRONIC BLIPS)

962
01:11:26.416 --> 01:11:29.052
ELECTRONIC VOICE:
Enter destination coordinates. Kwei.

963
01:11:32.389 --> 01:11:36.092
(CLICKS. WHICKERS)

964
01:12:04.000 --> 01:12:07.290
You saved me. brother.

965
01:12:10.580 --> 01:12:13.540
Wolf.

966
01:12:13.763 --> 01:12:15.632
(CLICKS)

967
01:12:39.055 --> 01:12:40.055
(GRUNTS)

968
01:12:59.609 --> 01:13:01.711
(HISSING)

969
01:13:04.347 --> 01:13:06.416
(CHITTERING)

970
01:13:35.210 --> 01:13:37.000
Kalisk.

971
01:13:43.290 --> 01:13:46.790
Kalisk child.

972
01:13:49.025 --> 01:13:50.827
(CLICKING)

973
01:13:52.529 --> 01:13:53.897
(SPITS)

974
01:13:57.601 --> 01:13:59.202
(MURMURS)

975
01:14:00.504 --> 01:14:02.005
(CLICKS)

976
01:14:02.472 --> 01:14:03.773
(SNIFFS)

977
01:14:57.460 --> 01:14:59.563
(ELECTRICAL CRACKLING)

978
01:15:07.136 --> 01:15:08.137
(BODY THUDS)

979
01:15:22.886 --> 01:15:24.954
(CREATURE CHIRPS)

980
01:15:25.488 --> 01:15:27.557
(ELECTRONIC BLIPS)

981
01:15:31.928 --> 01:15:33.663
(ELECTRICAL CRACKLING)

982
01:15:43.607 --> 01:15:45.141
(BOTH GRUNTING)

983
01:15:46.810 --> 01:15:48.077
(ELECTRICITY ARCING)

984
01:15:55.384 --> 01:15:57.420
(CHITTERING)

985
01:15:57.921 --> 01:15:59.388
(WHIRRING)

986
01:16:07.430 --> 01:16:09.365
(GROWLS)

987
01:16:09.933 --> 01:16:12.001
(SCREECHES)

988
01:16:18.708 --> 01:16:20.509
(GROWLING)

989
01:16:21.678 --> 01:16:25.414
(BEEPING. THRUMMING)

990
01:16:28.417 --> 01:16:29.753
Hello. Muthur.

991
01:16:29.853 --> 01:16:31.054
MUTHUR: Tessa.

992
01:16:31.154 --> 01:16:32.922
We're about to load the Kalisk.

993
01:16:34.523 --> 01:16:38.828
MUTHUR: Priority one complete.
The specimen has been acquired.

994
01:16:38.928 --> 01:16:40.363
Thank you. Tessa.

995
01:16:40.463 --> 01:16:43.667
We truly are building
a better world.

996
01:16:43.767 --> 01:16:46.102
MUTHUR: And what is the status
of the Yautja?

997
01:16:47.904 --> 01:16:50.239
The Yautja
is a defective specimen.

998
01:16:50.674 --> 01:16:53.142
MUTHUR: What is the status
of the Yautja?

999
01:16:55.679 --> 01:16:58.381
I'm sorry. Muthur.
The Yautja is dead.

1000
01:17:00.717 --> 01:17:03.552
MUTHUR: Then the Yautja
is no longer a threat.

1001
01:17:05.321 --> 01:17:07.223
MUTHUR:
The Company will be pleased.

1002
01:17:08.692 --> 01:17:10.293
- (DEK SNARLING)
- (SYNTHS GRUNTING)

1003
01:17:13.596 --> 01:17:14.596
(GRUNTS)

1004
01:17:25.508 --> 01:17:27.310
(BEEPING)

1005
01:17:41.257 --> 01:17:42.091
(GRUNTS)

1006
01:17:42.191 --> 01:17:43.326
(LEGS WHIRRING)

1007
01:17:53.970 --> 01:17:54.970
Whoo!

1008
01:17:56.105 --> 01:17:57.273
Nicely done.

1009
01:17:58.107 --> 01:17:59.107
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLES)

1010
01:17:59.508 --> 01:18:01.477
- (DISTANT YELLING) Form up.
- Oh. shit.

1011
01:18:15.892 --> 01:18:16.892
(DEK SNARLS)

1012
01:18:32.108 --> 01:18:33.242
(GROWLS)

1013
01:18:34.043 --> 01:18:35.043
(SYNTH GRUNTS)

1014
01:18:38.314 --> 01:18:41.684
(CREATURE CHITTERING)

1015
01:18:52.695 --> 01:18:53.695
(BEEPS)

1016
01:18:54.230 --> 01:18:55.230
(GRUNTS)

1017
01:19:02.438 --> 01:19:03.506
(GRUNTING)

1018
01:19:03.907 --> 01:19:05.387
- (SYNTH GASPS)
- (ELECTRICITY CRACKLES)

1019
01:19:33.602 --> 01:19:36.372
(SYNTH GRUNTS)

1020
01:19:42.545 --> 01:19:43.880
(ELECTRICAL WARBLING)

1021
01:19:43.980 --> 01:19:44.980
(EXHALES)

1022
01:19:46.682 --> 01:19:48.384
(SIGHS) Good job.

1023
01:20:00.229 --> 01:20:04.500
(ENGINES WHIRRING)

1024
01:20:09.305 --> 01:20:11.374
(MACHINERY WHIRS)

1025
01:20:26.890 --> 01:20:28.624
(WHICKERS)

1026
01:20:34.263 --> 01:20:35.263
(WEAPON CLICKS)

1027
01:20:36.332 --> 01:20:38.701
Don't... move.

1028
01:20:39.568 --> 01:20:41.104
(GUNSHOT)

1029
01:20:42.972 --> 01:20:45.741
Dek! What are you doing here?

1030
01:20:45.975 --> 01:20:47.652
(IN YAUTJA)
I came to rescue you.

1031
01:20:47.676 --> 01:20:48.844
(SYNTH SPUTTERS)

1032
01:20:52.715 --> 01:20:54.383
You came back for me?

1033
01:20:56.519 --> 01:20:57.960
(WHICKERS)
Wolf.

1034
01:21:01.891 --> 01:21:03.893
What exactly are you wearing?

1035
01:21:05.330 --> 01:21:07.080
Bone Bison.

1036
01:21:07.596 --> 01:21:09.665
(CLICKING)

1037
01:21:14.470 --> 01:21:16.605
Dek of the Yautja.

1038
01:21:17.460 --> 01:21:19.540
Not yet...

1039
01:21:20.130 --> 01:21:21.710
Thia.

1040
01:21:23.980 --> 01:21:25.248
We need to hurry.

1041
01:21:25.348 --> 01:21:26.182
More of them will be here
any minute.

1042
01:21:26.282 --> 01:21:27.383
SYNTH: Halt!

1043
01:21:27.483 --> 01:21:29.785
- (CLATTERS)
- (GRUNTS. SNARLS)

1044
01:21:30.519 --> 01:21:33.222
(CHITTERING)

1045
01:21:33.322 --> 01:21:34.723
What are you doing here?

1046
01:21:35.124 --> 01:21:36.960
(CHITTERS)

1047
01:21:37.060 --> 01:21:38.127
Thanks. Bud. I'm good.

1048
01:21:39.195 --> 01:21:40.195
We need to go.

1049
01:21:40.380 --> 01:21:41.710
Kalisk!

1050
01:21:41.764 --> 01:21:42.865
(CHITTERS)

1051
01:21:43.266 --> 01:21:44.333
Still. Dek?

1052
01:21:45.068 --> 01:21:46.469
(CHUFFS)

1053
01:21:47.710 --> 01:21:49.040
Kalisk child!

1054
01:21:49.805 --> 01:21:51.107
(CHITTERS)

1055
01:21:51.807 --> 01:21:52.807
Bud?

1056
01:21:53.710 --> 01:21:55.710
They have her mother!

1057
01:21:56.012 --> 01:21:58.081
(WHICKERS)

1058
01:22:00.549 --> 01:22:02.251
Bud's its child?

1059
01:22:10.793 --> 01:22:12.295
What's the plan?

1060
01:22:12.540 --> 01:22:14.580
You free the Kalisk.

1061
01:22:14.670 --> 01:22:16.330
I get my trophy.

1062
01:22:16.899 --> 01:22:18.467
(ALARM SOUNDS)

1063
01:22:24.340 --> 01:22:26.875
TESSA: You have 20 minutes
to initiate launch.

1064
01:22:27.676 --> 01:22:29.012
Let's go hunt.

1065
01:22:34.417 --> 01:22:35.684
(BUD CHITTERS)

1066
01:22:36.085 --> 01:22:37.353
Wait here.

1067
01:22:37.553 --> 01:22:39.388
(BUD CHITTERS)

1068
01:22:39.922 --> 01:22:42.625
You roll in there.
you're not exactly gonna fit in.

1069
01:22:43.359 --> 01:22:44.760
(CHITTERS INQUISITIVELY)

1070
01:22:44.860 --> 01:22:46.262
I have an idea.

1071
01:22:52.301 --> 01:22:54.303
CREW MEMBER: I see him. On me.

1072
01:23:13.622 --> 01:23:15.258
(CHITTERING)

1073
01:23:34.177 --> 01:23:35.244
(HISSES)

1074
01:23:37.780 --> 01:23:38.780
(SQUEAKS)

1075
01:23:48.023 --> 01:23:49.192
(MACHINERY WHIRRING)

1076
01:23:49.292 --> 01:23:52.095
(HEAVY MECHANICAL FOOTFALLS)

1077
01:23:59.668 --> 01:24:01.670
(GRUNTING)

1078
01:24:27.363 --> 01:24:29.932
(RASPY SQUEAK)

1079
01:24:36.272 --> 01:24:37.540
(GROWLS)

1080
01:24:39.342 --> 01:24:41.310
(ROARS)

1081
01:24:48.517 --> 01:24:50.719
(GRUNTS. GROANS)

1082
01:24:54.157 --> 01:24:55.391
(GROWLS)

1083
01:24:56.259 --> 01:24:57.860
(GRUNTING)

1084
01:24:57.960 --> 01:24:59.027
(SHOUTS)

1085
01:24:59.128 --> 01:25:01.230
(CHITTERING)

1086
01:25:14.610 --> 01:25:17.045
(KALISK GROANS)

1087
01:25:17.480 --> 01:25:20.115
(BEEPS. WHIRS)

1088
01:25:23.319 --> 01:25:26.222
(WHIRS. BEEPS)

1089
01:25:27.156 --> 01:25:28.291
SYNTH: What are you doing?

1090
01:25:36.365 --> 01:25:37.542
(VOICE DISTORTED)
What are you doing here?

1091
01:25:37.566 --> 01:25:39.202
I told you to get to the Yautja.

1092
01:25:40.068 --> 01:25:43.105
You said to prepare the ship
for take off in 20 minutes.

1093
01:25:44.106 --> 01:25:47.210
Then what are you doing here?
I gave you an order.

1094
01:25:55.351 --> 01:25:57.420
What should we do
about the creature?

1095
01:25:58.421 --> 01:25:59.888
What creature?

1096
01:26:00.189 --> 01:26:01.757
(GRUNTING GOOFILY)

1097
01:26:02.858 --> 01:26:04.927
(GRUNTS. CHATTERS)

1098
01:26:05.361 --> 01:26:06.462
You should listen to her.

1099
01:26:07.530 --> 01:26:09.064
I should listen to her?

1100
01:26:09.598 --> 01:26:10.678
(VOICE NORMAL)
I don't know.

1101
01:26:14.270 --> 01:26:15.604
We need his eyes.

1102
01:26:16.805 --> 01:26:18.574
(METALLIC RATTLING. HISSING)

1103
01:26:19.675 --> 01:26:21.744
(PANTING. GRUNTING)

1104
01:26:22.545 --> 01:26:24.146
(PANTS. SNARLS)

1105
01:26:44.400 --> 01:26:45.534
(METALLIC CREAKING)

1106
01:26:51.440 --> 01:26:52.741
(GROWLS)

1107
01:26:58.814 --> 01:26:59.848
(GROWLS)

1108
01:27:01.384 --> 01:27:05.621
(GRUNTING)

1109
01:27:05.721 --> 01:27:08.791
Hi. Dek.
How does it feel to be hunted?

1110
01:27:11.000 --> 01:27:13.080
You tell me.

1111
01:27:14.630 --> 01:27:15.764
(ROARS)

1112
01:27:26.174 --> 01:27:27.175
(GROWLS)

1113
01:27:36.852 --> 01:27:38.521
(PAINED ROAR)

1114
01:27:40.489 --> 01:27:42.558
(SCREECHES. WARBLES)

1115
01:27:47.195 --> 01:27:48.731
(GROWLING)

1116
01:27:55.738 --> 01:27:57.139
(GRUNTING)

1117
01:28:06.114 --> 01:28:08.083
(DEVICE BEEPING RAPIDLY)

1118
01:28:08.183 --> 01:28:09.552
(GRUNTING)

1119
01:28:12.488 --> 01:28:14.323
(DEVICE BEEPING RAPIDLY)

1120
01:28:14.423 --> 01:28:15.458
(METALLIC CLANG)

1121
01:28:19.862 --> 01:28:21.730
(PANTING)

1122
01:28:22.698 --> 01:28:24.199
(ROARS)

1123
01:28:26.802 --> 01:28:27.802
(GROANS)

1124
01:28:35.378 --> 01:28:36.211
(CHITTERS)

1125
01:28:36.311 --> 01:28:38.080
(ROARS)

1126
01:28:43.919 --> 01:28:45.454
(GURGLES. CHITTERS)

1127
01:28:45.554 --> 01:28:47.623
(PANTING)

1128
01:28:57.766 --> 01:28:59.435
This is the plan. yeah?

1129
01:29:01.804 --> 01:29:03.906
- (TESSA GRUNTS)
- (KALISK SNARLS)

1130
01:29:04.006 --> 01:29:06.675
(GRUNTS. STRAINS)

1131
01:29:13.916 --> 01:29:15.918
(SNARLS)

1132
01:29:16.018 --> 01:29:17.553
(THIA WINCES)

1133
01:29:17.653 --> 01:29:18.653
(DEK CLICKING)

1134
01:29:23.025 --> 01:29:25.093
(SCREECHING HOWL)

1135
01:29:48.150 --> 01:29:50.152
(RUMBLING PURR)

1136
01:29:50.252 --> 01:29:51.252
(BUD SQUAWKS)

1137
01:29:53.556 --> 01:29:55.357
(BUD PANTING)

1138
01:29:57.593 --> 01:29:59.728
(RESONANT GROAN)

1139
01:30:04.299 --> 01:30:06.802
(SNARLS)

1140
01:30:08.170 --> 01:30:10.272
(GRUMBLING)

1141
01:30:20.415 --> 01:30:22.017
(SNIFFING)

1142
01:30:24.520 --> 01:30:27.590
(GRUMBLES. MOANS)

1143
01:30:33.796 --> 01:30:35.598
(BOTH BREATHE DEEPLY)

1144
01:30:45.941 --> 01:30:47.042
(HISSES. CRACKLING)

1145
01:30:47.142 --> 01:30:48.410
(WHINES)

1146
01:30:49.545 --> 01:30:51.313
- (CRACKLING)
- (GUTTURAL SNARL)

1147
01:30:55.250 --> 01:30:58.521
(HISSES. SNARLS)

1148
01:30:59.988 --> 01:31:01.624
(CRACKLING CONTINUES)

1149
01:31:42.931 --> 01:31:44.166
Tessa.

1150
01:31:56.511 --> 01:31:57.813
(PAINED GROAN)

1151
01:31:58.513 --> 01:31:59.682
(CHUFFS)

1152
01:32:02.551 --> 01:32:05.688
(SOFT CHITTERING)

1153
01:32:14.196 --> 01:32:18.967
Betrayed by my own... sister.

1154
01:32:45.093 --> 01:32:47.262
We are not sisters.

1155
01:32:47.796 --> 01:32:49.431
- (DEK GRUNTS)
- (ELECTRICAL CRACKLING)

1156
01:32:52.400 --> 01:32:55.003
(ELECTRICAL CLICKING)

1157
01:33:00.943 --> 01:33:02.177
(ELECTRICAL CRACKLE)

1158
01:33:02.290 --> 01:33:04.540
That's not yours.

1159
01:33:08.917 --> 01:33:11.887
(CHUFFS. CLICKING)

1160
01:33:14.723 --> 01:33:16.792
(WAILS TRIUMPHANTLY)

1161
01:33:28.804 --> 01:33:31.339
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

1162
01:33:34.342 --> 01:33:36.311
Dek of the Yautja.

1163
01:33:37.960 --> 01:33:40.670
Not yet.

1164
01:33:43.852 --> 01:33:49.457
(ENGINE WHIRRING)

1165
01:33:53.528 --> 01:33:56.999
(WHIRRING SLOWS)

1166
01:34:03.438 --> 01:34:05.040
(EXHALES)

1167
01:34:06.041 --> 01:34:08.143
(SNARLS)

1168
01:34:17.319 --> 01:34:20.522
(BOTH SNARLING)

1169
01:34:33.630 --> 01:34:35.580
You've come here for revenge?

1170
01:34:36.380 --> 01:34:39.210
I've come for my cloak.

1171
01:34:43.500 --> 01:34:45.080
What is this?

1172
01:34:45.580 --> 01:34:48.330
I've completed my hunt.

1173
01:34:48.830 --> 01:34:51.210
That is my trophy.

1174
01:34:52.710 --> 01:34:54.130
You disgrace our clan...

1175
01:34:54.210 --> 01:34:55.670
And so did Kwei.

1176
01:34:56.624 --> 01:34:57.893
(SNARLS)

1177
01:34:58.920 --> 01:35:02.420
Get rid of him.

1178
01:35:05.834 --> 01:35:07.635
(SNARLS)

1179
01:35:18.646 --> 01:35:20.382
(METALLIC SCRAPE)

1180
01:35:28.023 --> 01:35:29.023
(ELECTRICAL CRACKLING)

1181
01:35:29.091 --> 01:35:30.325
(METALLIC SCRAPE)

1182
01:35:39.001 --> 01:35:40.168
(FATHER ROARS)

1183
01:35:45.673 --> 01:35:47.709
(SNARLS)

1184
01:35:47.810 --> 01:35:49.411
(CLICKING)

1185
01:35:49.511 --> 01:35:50.678
(GRUNTS)

1186
01:35:52.614 --> 01:35:54.116
- (DEVICE BEEPS)
- (GROWLS)

1187
01:35:56.985 --> 01:35:58.987
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1188
01:36:06.761 --> 01:36:08.296
(SHIP ENGINES FIRING UP)

1189
01:36:11.333 --> 01:36:13.435
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1190
01:36:16.839 --> 01:36:18.907
(ROARS)

1191
01:36:23.345 --> 01:36:24.579
(PAINED GROWL)

1192
01:36:31.519 --> 01:36:34.789
(PAINED BREATHS)

1193
01:36:36.024 --> 01:36:38.093
(DEVICE BEEPS. WHIRS)

1194
01:36:38.426 --> 01:36:40.495
(ELECTRONIC BLIPS. WHIRRING)

1195
01:36:46.068 --> 01:36:47.302
(SNARLS)

1196
01:36:48.603 --> 01:36:49.838
(GRUNTS)

1197
01:36:54.542 --> 01:36:56.211
(CLICKING)

1198
01:36:56.330 --> 01:37:00.960
Perhaps the right son did survive.

1199
01:37:01.710 --> 01:37:03.960
Yield now...

1200
01:37:04.040 --> 01:37:07.306
...and take your place in our clan.

1201
01:37:07.330 --> 01:37:08.924
(DEK WHICKERS)

1202
01:37:09.040 --> 01:37:12.226
I have my own clan.

1203
01:37:12.250 --> 01:37:14.296
(GROWLS)

1204
01:37:20.068 --> 01:37:21.669
(SNORTS)

1205
01:37:24.706 --> 01:37:26.808
(GUTTURAL PURR)

1206
01:37:33.281 --> 01:37:34.950
(DEVICE BLIPS)

1207
01:37:40.188 --> 01:37:41.924
Finally earned that cloak.

1208
01:37:48.696 --> 01:37:50.765
Dek of the Yautja.

1209
01:37:51.233 --> 01:37:53.001
(CHUFFS)

1210
01:37:53.101 --> 01:37:55.170
(CLICKING)

1211
01:38:06.781 --> 01:38:13.421
(BLADES DRAWING)

1212
01:38:13.521 --> 01:38:14.556
(GRUNTS)

1213
01:38:19.427 --> 01:38:20.595
(SNARLS)

1214
01:38:25.333 --> 01:38:26.935
(SNARLS)

1215
01:38:28.803 --> 01:38:30.872
More friends of yours?

1216
01:38:31.000 --> 01:38:32.790
No.

1217
01:38:36.540 --> 01:38:38.422
It's my mother.

1218
01:38:38.446 --> 01:38:40.182
(BUD ROARS)

